text:
I know people using GitHub copilot for HubSpot CMS development as well as any other development and they find it very handy

Is there anything in particular you're interested in?
I was wondering how useful it is in particular with hubl. And/ or if there are any other AI tools you'd recommend

I know <@UN7CEHC9X> uses copilot on a daily basis. From what I hear from him, this $10 subscription was worth it.

If you want to automate the processes instead of relying on your memory, copilot can help with that.
Sometimes, particularly with hubl it might be a bit quirky by misspelling the properties. So you need to pay attention to what it adds to your code
Using gpt and <http://Blackbox.ai|Blackbox.ai> from time to time. Not for writing hubl but for other class stuff

I use copilot, definitely worth the $10. 

It does pretty good with HubL, but it does sprinkle in a little bit of jinja. And sometimes it doesn't work
